<br>
I would further suggest this, as mutant and I have kicked around already, why not update Mordheim rules a little so they are in line with the current edition of Warhammer Fantasy. More particularly, update the weapon rules from the current Mordheim rulebook to Warhammer 6th(?) edition. For example:<br>
<br>
Sword: can parry, but also counts as a hand weapon for an additional +1 save if the model has a sheild<br>
<br>
Axe: -1 armor save but also counts as a hand weapon for shield/save purposes<br>
<br>
mace, hammer: stun bonus but also hand weapon for save puposes<br>
<br>
Great weapon: strikes first on the charge, but always last thereafter<br>
<br>
Basically, would keep all the mordheim weapon rules, but would make the addition to bring them in line to the current version of Warhammer.<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
